        "<!-- @answer:S2R -->\n",
        "*(write your answer here — do not delete this cell)* --- I learned that to access certain information, I need to use iloc or just loc. loc is for things thata are labled like dates or things like 'a' 'b' etc for strincs where as iloc is for when i am getting the location of certain columns/rows I can use index when pulling r/c this way. Since .loc pulls all columns for 02-04 it includes both those dates in the range where as .iloc uses index where it is non inclusive. ( only rows 3,4 will show up )"
